gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Pelicans 96, Knicks 87
gameRecap.excerpt: The Pelicans defeated the Knicks, 96-87. Brandon Ingram recorded 26 points (11-17 FG) and seven rebounds for the Pelicans, while Zion Williamson added 24 points (12-17 FG) and five rebounds in the victory. RJ Barrett tallied a team-high 18 points, along with three rebounds and two assists for the Knicks in the losing effort. The Pelicans improve to 2-0 on the season, while the Knicks fall to 1-2.
